HEADWORD: Uncrudded
<hw>Un*crud"ded</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Un-</er>
not, and <er>Curd</er>.]</ety> <def>Not cruddled, or curdled.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her breast like to a bowl of cream <qex>uncrudded</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

